"{\"uid\": \"cbc.ca-news-canada-manitoba-paris-olympics-triathlete-tyler-mislawchuk-1.7281092\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A Manitoba Olympian hopes his performance at the 2024 Paris\\u00a0Olympic Games will inspire young athletes in the province and across the country.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\", \"score\": 0.9999995165700316, \"rank\": 4.833852548220013e-07, \"text\": \"Manitoba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\"}, {\"begin\": 11, \"end\": 19, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.998456833244434, \"rank\": 0.0015455517994337566, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Wednesday, Tyler Mislawchuk\\u00a0of Oak Bluff, a small community just southwest of Winnipeg,\\u00a0becamethe first Canadian Olympian to finish in the Top 10 of the men's triathlon since 2008, when Simon Whitfield won silver in Beijing.\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 157, \"end\": 173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tyler Mislawchuk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\"}, {\"begin\": 181, \"end\": 186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"score\": 0.9976461160870269, \"rank\": 0.0023594377557234736, \"text\": \"Bluff\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\"}, {\"begin\": 250, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.715220571614503, \"rank\": 0.3961589033811217, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 259, \"end\": 267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.998456833244434, \"rank\": 0.0015455517994337566, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simon_Whitfield\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simon Whitfield\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simon_Whitfield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simon_Whitfield\"}, {\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998830744585, \"rank\": 1.1692566278542131e-07, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old secured a ninth-place result in the event, after finishing 15th at both the 2016 Rio Olympic Games and the 2020 Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am from Oak Bluff, Manitoba.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"score\": 0.9976461160870269, \"rank\": 0.0023594377557234736, \"text\": \"Bluff\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\"}, {\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\", \"score\": 0.9999995165700316, \"rank\": 4.833852548220013e-07, \"text\": \"Manitoba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's -55 in the winter - school closed,\\u00a0[you] climb through snow banks to get to school,\\\" he told CBC Sports\\u00a0after the event, which features a\\u00a01.5-kilometre\\u00a0swim, a 40-kilometre bike ride and a 10-kilometre run.\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999972317284237, \"rank\": 2.768279173347169e-06, \"text\": \"CBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am here at the Summer Olympics, the biggest sporting stage in the world, and \\u2026 I started at [the]Manitoba Games.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 874, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not even get on the podium at Manitoba Games, and I [fought] for a medal at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"No matter where you are at your level \\u2026 do not give up.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Keep fighting.\\\"\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Keep fighting\\\" \\ud83d\\ude24<br><br>Tyler Mislawchuk hopes to inspire Canadians after his incredible top 10 triathlon finish at <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/Paris2024?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\\">#Paris2024</a><br><br>More: <a href=\\\"https://t.co/EZLPmMGGpC\\\">https://t.co/EZLPmMGGpC</a> <a href=\\\"https://t.co/FrHo7vdgDD\\\">pic.twitter.com/FrHo7vdgDD</a>  Mislawchukposted on Instagramprior to the Olympics that he hoped the third time would be the charm, after his previous appearances at the Olympic Games in\\u00a0Tokyo,\\u00a0where his hopes for a podium finish were dashed when he was injured during the race, and in Rio.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tyler Mislawchuk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\"}, {\"begin\": 1556, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998853850720152, \"rank\": 0.00011054134538162212, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1655, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999856140352916, \"rank\": 1.4386171733248474e-05, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am proud of the effort,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1696, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mislawchuk has had supporters back home cheering him on.\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Members of the province's triathlon community gathered along a service road in Oak Bluff, where Mislawchuk trained, on Monday, when the triathlon event was originally scheduled to take place.\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"score\": 0.9976461160870269, \"rank\": 0.0023594377557234736, \"text\": \"Bluff\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Itwas postponedto Wednesday over concerns about water quality in the Seine River, where the swimming portion of the race took place.\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 2080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are so lucky with Tyler as an ambassador for our sport and \\u2026 for our province,\\\" Triathlon Manitoba executive director Jared Spier said on Monday.\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2105, \"end\": 2110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tyler\", \"score\": 0.9997097087856075, \"rank\": 0.0001389146164932074, \"text\": \"Tyler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tyler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Tyler\"}, {\"begin\": 2167, \"end\": 2176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.687078446902117e-23, \"text\": \"Triathlon\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\", \"score\": 0.9999995165700316, \"rank\": 4.833852548220013e-07, \"text\": \"Manitoba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manitoba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's exactly who you want to cheer for.\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's hard-working, he's well-spoken.\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's got no ego about him.\\u2026 It's great to have everybody behind him, because it's so easy to get behind him.\\\"\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Mislawchuk\\u00a0- who said he\\u00a0always races until \\\"the wheels come off\\\"\\u00a0-\\u00a0said he's grateful for the people who never stopped believing in him along the way, and hopes it may help inspire others.\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If some kid in Oak Bluff,\\u00a0Man., or Quebec\\u00a0or B.C.\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"score\": 0.9976461160870269, \"rank\": 0.0023594377557234736, \"text\": \"Bluff\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uptown_Pittsburgh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"can take a little bit of inspiration of how I fought out there, then job done.\\\"\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With files from CBC Sports and Cameron MacLean  Audience Relations, CBCP.O.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2773, \"end\": 2783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999972317284237, \"rank\": 2.768279173347169e-06, \"text\": \"CBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2788, \"end\": 2795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"score\": 0.9999999978231244, \"rank\": 2.1767537200754368e-09, \"text\": \"Cameron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Box 500 Station AToronto, ONCanada, M5W 1E6  Toll-free (Canada only):1-866-306-4636  It is a priority for CBC to create products that are accessible to all in Canada including people with visual, hearing, motor and cognitive challenges.\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 3068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2939, \"end\": 2942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.6049335339850607, \"rank\": 0.6266004470875356, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\"}, {\"b